Title : Kilbella Bay
Text : '''Kilbella Bay''' is a [[bay]] on the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast of British Columbia]], Canada, off the north side of [[Rivers Inlet]] to the northeast of [[McAllister Point]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/26517.html BC Names/GeoBC "Kilbella Bay (bay)"]</ref>  A [[Steamboat|steamer]] landing formerly operated by the [[Northland Navigation Company]] was located on the east side of the bay.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/26516.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Kilbella Bay (landing)"]</ref>

The [[Kilbella River|Kilbella]] and [[Chuckwalla River]]s both enter the sea at Kilbella Bay.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/3835.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Kilbella River"]</ref><ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/26769.html BC Names/GeobC entry "Chuckwalla River"]</ref>

The location is within the traditional territory of the [[Wuikinuxv]].  '''Kiltala Indian Reserve No. 2''', one of their [[Indian reserve]]s, is located at the mouth of the Kilbella River.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/64426.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Kiltala 2 (Indian reserve)"]</ref>

